"l.u.-" en comments "The trace reveals in the matter the signature of a moving cause: prints, vibrations, modulations, fragments, wakes, drops, smells. While the mark - a sign in time - was made on purpose to last, the trace is often unintentional and can be transient, like a child's run that prints itself for a moment on snow or sand. It's the sign in space. Although resulting from the fortuitous contact of things or natural causality, it does not signal with less certainty the existence of its object: smoke denounces fire."
